Visualization of Stochastic Processes

Wenyao Sha

2018-05-23



Stochastic process makes for an excellent source of visualization. In this post, I show the dynamics of stochastic processes along the three physical diemensions:

  • \(t\): time
  • \(x\): the value of the stochastic process at time \(t\)
  • \(f(x)\): the probability density of \(x\) at time \(t\)

Note that the expected value at each time \(t\) is also highlighted.

Drag to rotate and scroll to zoom in/out on WebGL-compatable devices. Certain feature like drift, dispersion, mean-reversion or non-negativeness might only be visible from a different angle.



Trend Stationary Model (without Drift)

\(X_t = X_0 + \epsilon_t\)





Trend Stationary Model

\(X_t = X_0 + \beta t + \epsilon_t\)





Brownian Motion (without Drift)

\(dX_t = \sigma dW_t\)





Brownian Motion

\(dX_t = \mu t + \sigma dW_t\)





Geometric Brwonian Motion

\(dX_t = \mu X_t t + \sigma X_t dW_t\)





Vasicek Model

\(dX_t = a(b-X_t)dt + \sigma dW_t\)





CoxIngersollRoss Model

\(dX_t = a(b-X_t)dt + \sigma \sqrt{X_t}dW_t\)
